{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T09:09:15.082Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Cosine Annealing — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Cosine Annealing Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cosine Annealing"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a learning rate scheduling technique that smoothly decreases the learning rate following a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "cosine curve"}, {"type": "text", "text": " from a maximum value to a minimum value."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The learning rate follows a smooth periodic curve shaped like a cosine wave. Instead of step-wise or linear decay, it uses a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "continuous, smooth function"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that decreases the learning rate in a cosine pattern."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Cosine Annealing Matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cosine annealing is one of the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "most practical learning-rate schedules"}, {"type": "text", "text": " used in deep learning today, offering significant benefits:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Effect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Faster convergence"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Smooth decay avoids abrupt changes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transformers, LLMs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Better generalization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Helps escape local minima"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Vision models, diffusion"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stable training"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Smooth transitions prevent instability"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large models, mixed precision"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Low-cost, high-impact"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Minimal tuning needed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All deep learning"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Robust hyperparameters"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Works well with default values"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "General deep learning"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In 2025, with larger models and mixed-precision training common, learning-rate scheduling remains a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "low-cost, high-impact lever"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to stabilize and speed up training."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Cosine Annealing Works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Core Formula"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The learning rate at step "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "t"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " follows this cosine curve:"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\eta_t = \\eta_{\\min} + \\frac{1}{2}(\\eta_{\\max} - \\eta_{\\min}) \\left(1 + \\cos\\left(\\frac{\\pi \\cdot T_{\\text{cur}}}{T_{\\max}}\\right)\\right)"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\eta_t"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Learning rate at step "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "t"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\eta_{\\min}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Minimum learning rate (e.g., 0 or 1e-6)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\eta_{\\max}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Maximum learning rate (initial LR)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "T_{\\text{cur}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Number of epochs/steps since last restart\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "T_{\\max}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Maximum number of epochs in a cycle\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\pi"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Pi (180°)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Shape of the Curve"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "LR\nη_max |⮕⮕⮕⮕⮕⮕⮕⮕⮕⮕\n      |  \\      /\n      |   \\    /\n      |    \\  /\n      |     \\/\nη_min |      ⮕\n      +------------------→ Epoch\n       0    50   100"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Starts at maximum"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\eta_{\\max}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " at "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "T_{\\text{cur}} = 0"}}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Decreases smoothly"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Follows cosine curve to minimum"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ends at minimum"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\eta_{\\min}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " at "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "T_{\\text{cur}} = T_{\\max}"}}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Smooth transitions"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": No abrupt jumps"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cosine Annealing SR (SGDR) with Warm Restarts"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Introduction to Warm Restarts"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cosine Annealing with Warm Restarts"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (also called "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGDR"}, {"type": "text", "text": ") periodically resets the learning rate back to the maximum after reaching the minimum:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# With restarts (SGDR)\n# Cycle 1: η_max → η_min (cosine)\n# Restart: η_min → η_max (sudden jump)\n# Cycle 2: η_max → η_min (cosine)\n# ..."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Benefits"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Approaches minimal loss closer"}, {"type": "text", "text": " with each restart\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Takes good weights"}, {"type": "text", "text": " from previous cycle as starting point\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Escapes local minima"}, {"type": "text", "text": " more effectively"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Without Restarts (Standard Cosine Annealing)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The standard PyTorch implementation performs cosine annealing "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "without restarts"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Without restarts\n# η_max → η_min (smooth cosine decay)\n# No periodic resets"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cosine Annealing in PyTorch"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard Cosine Annealing (No Restarts)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\nimport torch.optim as optim\nfrom torch.optim.lr_scheduler import CosineAnnealingLR\n\nmodel = torch.nn.Linear(10, 1)\noptimizer = optim.SGD(model.parameters(), lr=0.1)\n\n# Cosine annealing scheduler\nscheduler = CosineAnnealingLR(\n    optimizer,\n    T_max=100,         # Maximum epochs in cycle [web:195]\n    eta_min=0.0        # Minimum learning rate [web:195]\n)\n\n# Training loop\nfor epoch in range(100):\n    train_epoch()\n    valid_epoch()\n    scheduler.step()  # Update learning rate [web:195]\n    lr = scheduler.get_last_lr()[0]\n    print(f\"Epoch {epoch}, LR: {lr}\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cosine Annealing with Warm Restarts (SGDR)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from torch.optim.lr_scheduler import CosineAnnealingWarmRestarts\n\nmodel = torch.nn.Linear(10, 1)\noptimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001)\n\n# Cosine annealing with warm restarts\nscheduler = CosineAnnealingWarmRestarts(\n    optimizer,\n    T_0=10,            # First cycle length (epochs) [web:196]\n    T_mult=1,          # Multiplier for cycle length [web:196]\n    eta_min=1e-8       # Minimum learning rate [web:196]\n)\n\n# Training loop\nfor epoch in range(100):\n    train_epoch()\n    valid_epoch()\n    scheduler.step(epoch)  # Must pass epoch for restarts [web:196]\n    lr = scheduler.get_last_lr()[0]\n    print(f\"Epoch {epoch}, LR: {lr}\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cosine Annealing with Warmup"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import math\n\ndef cosine_with_warmup(epoch, total_epochs, warmup_epochs, lr_max, lr_min):\n    if epoch < warmup_epochs:\n        # Linear warmup\n        return lr_min + (lr_max - lr_min) * (epoch / warmup_epochs)\n    else:\n        # Cosine decay\n        progress = (epoch - warmup_epochs) / (total_epochs - warmup_epochs)\n        return lr_min + 0.5 * (lr_max - lr_min) * (1 + math.cos(math.pi * progress))\n\n# Training loop\nlr_max = 0.1\nlr_min = 1e-6\ntotal_epochs = 100\nwarmup_epochs = 10\n\nfor epoch in range(total_epochs):\n    lr = cosine_with_warmup(epoch, total_epochs, warmup_epochs, lr_max, lr_min)\n    for param_group in optimizer.param_groups:\n        param_group['lr'] = lr\n    train_epoch()"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cosine Annealing in TensorFlow/Keras"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using CosineDecay"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import tensorflow as tf\n\ntotal_epochs = 100\nlr_max = 0.1\nlr_min = 1e-6\n\n# Cosine decay schedule\nlr_schedule = tf.keras.optimizers.schedules.CosineDecay(\n    lr_max,              # Initial learning rate\n    total_epochs,        # Decay steps\n    alpha=lr_min / lr_max  # Minimum LR factor [web:195]\n)\n\noptimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=lr_schedule)\n\nmodel.fit(train_data, train_labels, epochs=total_epochs, optimizer=optimizer)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "With Warmup + Cosine Decay"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def cosine_with_warmup(step, warmup_steps, total_steps, lr_max, lr_min):\n    if step < warmup_steps:\n        # Linear warmup\n        return lr_min + (lr_max - lr_min) * (step / warmup_steps)\n    else:\n        # Cosine decay\n        progress = (step - warmup_steps) / (total_steps - warmup_steps)\n        return lr_min + 0.5 * (lr_max - lr_min) * (1 + math.cos(math.pi * progress))\n\ntotal_steps = 10000\nwarmup_steps = 1000\nlr_max = 0.1\nlr_min = 1e-6\n\nlr_schedule = lambda step: cosine_with_warmup(\n    step, warmup_steps, total_steps, lr_max, lr_min\n)\n\noptimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=lr_schedule)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Parameters"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Parameter"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Typical Value"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Purpose"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "η"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "italic"}], "text": "max (lr_max)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0.01–0.1"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Maximum learning rate (initial)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "η"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "italic"}], "text": "min (lr_min)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0 or 1e-6"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Minimum learning rate"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "T_max (epochs)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "50–300"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Total training epochs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "T_0 (restarts)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "10–50"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "First cycle length"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "T_mult"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1–2"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multiplier for cycle length"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "alpha"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "lr_min/lr_max"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Minimum LR factor in TensorFlow"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cosine Annealing vs. Other Schedules"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{